{"questionId":"3006089","questionHtml":"<p>Find the exact coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> and the exact value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempts to solve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></msup></mfenced><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math></p>\n<p>coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>)</mo></math> (accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> analytically&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>⇒</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>for example, writes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></msup></math> and then attempts to apply appropriate index/log laws to both sides: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo> </mo></mrow></msub><mtext>e</mtext></mrow></mfrac></math> and so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>&nbsp;for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> analytically &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></msup></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></mstyle></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>)</mo></math> (accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>(equation of the tangent at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>)</mo></math> is) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> (or equivalent)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>compares this equation with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> and attempts to form at least one of the following&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<br>attempts to solve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math></p>\n<p>coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>)</mo></math> (accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>e</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> (or equivalent) for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> analytically&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msup><m